<title>SWEDEN: Sandvik H1 fell but sees sales pick-up.</title>
<headline>Sandvik H1 fell but sees sales pick-up.</headline>
<dateline>STOCKHOLM 1997-08-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Swedish speciality toolmaker and engineer Sandvik AB on Tuesday posted an 18 percent fall in profits for the first half of the year but said order intake and sales rose considerably in the second quarter.</p>
<p>Sandvik said the favourable sales trend would continue in the second half of 1997.</p>
<p>&quot;However as a result of negative net financial items during the second half of the year, due mainly to share redemption, profit after financial items and expenses in 1997 is estimated to be largely unchanged compared with 1996,&quot; the company said in a statement.</p>
</text>
